Day 7: Intensive Codeforces Practice + Review
Objective: Apply all Week 2 knowledge in real contest-style problems.

Review (1 hour): Go through journal, rewrite one program from each day.
Practice (3 hours):
Solve 15 problems total (rating 800–1000):
Recommended list:
50A – “Domino piling”
263A – “Beautiful Matrix”
266B – “Queue at the School”
546A – “Soldier and Bananas”
677A – “Vanya and Fence”
734A – “Anton and Danik”
110A – “Nearly Lucky Number”
122A – “Lucky Division”
148A – “Insomnia cure”
155A – “I_love_%username%”


For each wrong submission: read editorial, understand mistake, rewrite correctly.

Analysis (45 minutes):
Journal: What topics were used? Common time-wasters? New tricks learned?
Goal: Successfully solve at least 12 out of 15.


Week 2 Milestone:

Comfortable with vectors, pairs, sorting, functions with references.
Solved 40–50 problems total so far.
Ready for greedy algorithms and more data structures in Week 3.

Keep the momentum – you’re building the core toolkit for competitive programming!
